#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:1
msgid "Persistent Identifiers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:3
msgid ""
"The [Persistent Identifiers "
"module](https://omeka.org/s/modules/PersistentIdentifiers/){target=_blank}"
" allows users to create or import persistent identifiers (PIDs) and "
"assign them to Omeka S items. These PIDs can be assigned at item "
"creation, via the item edit screen, or by batch edit. They can also be "
"removed using the item edit or batch edit screens. PIDs may also be "
"\"extracted\" from existing metadata fields. Once assigned, accessing an "
"item's PID in-browser resolves to a stable, non-site-specific landing "
"page containing the item's metadata, media, and any sites the item is "
"assigned to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:5
msgid "The current PID services available for this module are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:7
msgid "EZID (used to mint and manage Archival Resource Keys [ARKs])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:8
msgid "DataCite (used to mint and manage Digital Object Identifiers [DOIs])."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:10
msgid "General settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:12
msgid ""
"After installation, Persistent Identifiers should appear in the left-hand"
" navigation under **Modules**. The \"Settings\" subpage features general "
"settings, including:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:14
msgid ""
"**PID Service**: Select which of the available PID services to use for "
"minting or extraction. Only one PID service may be used at a time to mint"
" and assign PIDs to items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:15
msgid ""
"**Assign PID to New Items**: Check this box to automatically newly mint "
"or extract an existing PID and assign to every new item in Omeka S, "
"whether it is created in Omeka S or imported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:16
msgid ""
"**Fields with Existing PIDs**: A list of metadata fields separated by "
"commas that may contain PID values within a newly created or imported "
"item. If found, the existing PID will be assigned to the item instead of "
"a new PID."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:18
msgid ""
"![Configuration options for general "
"settings](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_settings.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:20
msgid "EZID configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:22
msgid ""
"When completing the configuration process for EZID, you will need to "
"provide the:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:24
msgid ""
"**NAAN & Shoulder Namespace**: The Name Assigning Authority Number (NAAN)"
" and ARK shoulder value uniquely assigned to an organization, which will "
"appear in every ARK generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:25
msgid ""
"**EZID Username**: The EZID user who has permission to create and update "
"identifiers for the above namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:26
msgid ""
"**EZID Password**: The password for the above EZID user. Note that for "
"security reasons this password doesn't persist in the form, so if changes"
" are made to the **NAAN & Shoulder Namespace** or **EZID Username** you "
"must also re-enter the password before pressing \"submit\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:28
msgid ""
"![EZID specific configuration "
"options](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_EZIDconfig.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:30
msgid "DataCite configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:32
msgid ""
"When completing the configuration process for DataCite, you will need to "
"provide the:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:34
msgid ""
"**Repository DOI Prefix**: The prefix assigned to an institution's DOI "
"minting and management repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:35
msgid ""
"**DataCite Repository ID**: The unique identifier assigned to an "
"institution's DOI repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:36
msgid ""
"**DataCite Password**: The password associated with the above **DataCite "
"Repository ID**. Note that for security reasons this password doesn't "
"persist in the form, so if changes are made to any field on the DataCite "
"Configuration screen, you must also re-enter the password before pressing"
" \"submit\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:38
msgid ""
"![DataCite specific configuration "
"options](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_DataCiteconfig.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:40
msgid "DataCite required metadata"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:42
msgid ""
"DataCite requires five descriptive metadata values in order to generate a"
" DOI: Title, Creators, Publisher, Publication Year, and Resource Type. "
"All of these fields must be mapped to an existing metadata field that you"
" select from the list of available vocabularies in your Omeka S instance."
" The Resource Type General property must conform to a "
"[ResourceTypeGeneral controlled "
"vocabulary](https://support.datacite.org/docs/datacite-metadata-"
"schema-v44-mandatory-properties#101-resourcetypegeneral){target=_blank} "
"value exactly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:44
msgid "Minting and removing PIDs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:46
msgid ""
"To mint a PID from the item edit page, click on an item and select \"Edit"
" Item.\" Navigate to the Advanced tab, and click \"Mint PID.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:48
msgid ""
"![Minting PIDs via Edit Item Advanced "
"tab](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_mint.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:50
msgid ""
"After a few moments, the ARK or DOI should appear. The \"Mint PID\" "
"button should now be a \"Remove PID\" button. Click here to remove the "
"PID."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:52
msgid ""
"![Removing PIDs via Edit Item Advanced "
"tab](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_remove.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:54
msgid ""
"If you select \"Remove PID,\" a drawer will open on the right warning you"
" that this will remove the PID and break any incoming links. Click "
"\"Confirm Remove PID\" to delete the PID."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:56
msgid ""
"![Drawer asking to confirm PID "
"removal](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_confirmremove.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:58
msgid ""
"Click \"Save\" before navigating away from the page when both minting and"
" removing PIDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:60
msgid "Batch editing PIDs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:62
msgid ""
"You can batch edit PIDs from the Items page. Select the items with PIDs "
"you wish to edit via the checkboxes, then choose \"Edit Selected\" before"
" pressing \"Go.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:64
msgid ""
"![Accessing batch edit from Items "
"page](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_batcheditgo.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:66
msgid ""
"Near the bottom of the Batch Edit Items screen, you should see a "
"Persistent Identifiers row. Here, you can mint or remove PIDs for all "
"selected items. If you are batch editing other fields and would like PIDs"
" to remain unaffected, you can select \"[no action]\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:68
msgid "![Batch edit items options](../modules/modulesfiles/PID_batchoptions.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/persistentidentifiers.md:70
msgid ""
"When you have made all desired edits, click \"Save\" in the upper right "
"corner."
msgstr ""

